==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Umbilicated
<hw>Um*bil"i*ca`ted</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>umbilicatus</ets>. See
<er>Umbilic</er>.]</ety> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Depressed in the middle, like
a navel, as a flower, fruit, or leaf; navel-shaped; having an umbilicus;
<as>as, an <ex>umbilicated</ex> smallpox vesicle</as>.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Supported by a stalk at the central
point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Umbilication</ent>⟦br⟧
